Start MongoDB
- Run sudo systemctl start mongod to start MongoDB.
- Run sudo systemctl daemon-reload to reload the systemd daemon.
- Run sudo systemctl status mongod to check the status of MongoDB.

Enable MongoDB to Start Automatically
- Run sudo systemctl enable mongod to enable MongoDB to start automatically on boot.

Start Mongosh
- Run mongosh to start the MongoDB shell.

Create a Database
- Run use <database_name> to create a new database or switch to an existing one.
- Run db.collection.insert({name: "<name>", year: <year>}) to add a document to the database.

Check Error Logs
- Run sudo tail -f /var/log/mongodb/mongod.log to check the error logs.

Uninstall MongoDB
- Run sudo service mongod stop to stop MongoDB.
- Run sudo apt purge "mongodb-org*" to uninstall MongoDB and remove all configuration files.
- Run sudo rm -r /var/log/mongodb and sudo rm -r /var/lib/mongodb to remove the MongoDB log and data directories.